          <p>The Michigan Women's Assembly (1975-1986, .3 linear feet) is a political coalition of women's groups from across the state. The Michigan Conference of NOW was one these groups. The assembly adopted platforms in 1982, 1984 and 1986 to bring attention to women's issues. As president of the Michigan Conference of NOW, Hays-Hamilton participated in some of the leadership activities of the assembly such as a retreat for the leadership to plan strategy.</p>
